When I (the person responding) was 6 years old, my sister was exactly half my age. This means that if we subtract 6 years from her current age (which is 80), we will get the age she was when I was 6. Let's calculate this step by step:

1. Subtract my current age (80) from her current age (80):
   Her current age - My current age = 80 - 6 = 74 years

So, my sister is now 74 years old.
